# Credit Card Fraud Detection using Unsupervised Machine Learning

## Overview

This project detects fraudulent credit card transactions using anomaly detection techniques without relying on labels during training.

The model learns normal transaction patterns and identifies unusual transactions as potential fraud.

---

## Dataset

- European credit card transactions
- 284,807 transactions
- Highly imbalanced dataset

---

## Features

- Data preprocessing
- Exploratory Data Analysis
- Feature scaling
- Isolation Forest
- Anomaly detection
- Performance evaluation
- Risk scoring

---

